      "dimensions": 1,
      "description": "playmode -  - Specifies the method used to playback the audio, there are 3 options.\n\n locked - This mode locks the playback position to the timeline. Scrubbing or jumping in the timeline will change the song position accordingly. The parameters Play, Reset, Speed, and Index are disabled in this mode since the timeline is directly tied to playback position. specify - This mode allows the user to specify a particular position in the song using the Index parameter below. Use this mode for random access to any location in the audio stream. sequential - This mode continually plays regardless of the timeline position (the Index parameter is disabled). Reset and Speed parameters below are enabled to allow some control. timecodeop - This mode allows the user to set the movie index by reference to a timecode in the form of either a , , or Timecode Class object.",
      "tooltip": "",
      "help": "",
      "units": "",
      "examples": [],
